1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,580
This series is crafted for the purpose of entertainment.

2
00:00:02,580 --> 00:00:04,820
All characters, behaviours, settings, and events depicted in this drama are entirely fictitious.

3
00:00:04,820 --> 00:00:06,660
They are not designed to allude to any particular entity, occupation, or group of people.

4
00:00:06,660 --> 00:00:09,980
Viewer discretion is advised.

5
00:00:10,020 --> 00:00:13,110
[North Star Entertainment]

6
00:00:13,110 --> 00:00:14,980
[IQIYI]

7
00:00:15,150 --> 00:00:17,180
[Present]

8
00:00:19,550 --> 00:00:26,510
♫Never met anyone who could make me understand this word♫

9
00:00:27,880 --> 00:00:34,780
♫But when I met you, my heart started beating fast♫

10
00:00:36,010 --> 00:00:43,180
♫You’re the only one in my heart who could make me feel this way♫

11
00:00:44,380 --> 00:00:50,910
♫This long-awaitied moment is now over♫

12
00:00:52,080 --> 00:00:56,350
♫From now on, my heart and soul will be yours for the rest of my life♫

13
00:00:56,350 --> 00:00:59,680
♫Always have each other, never let go♫

14
00:01:00,050 --> 00:01:04,750
♫Trust in me ‘cause I’ll be by your side♫

15
00:01:04,750 --> 00:01:09,780
♫Hold my hand, Baby♫

16
00:01:09,780 --> 00:01:12,980
[Desires in the Wind]

17
00:01:13,930 --> 00:01:16,650
[Previously]
Lom told me to get you. We have to go now.

18
00:01:16,800 --> 00:01:17,600
They’re there!

19
00:01:19,300 --> 00:01:20,710
Look out, Miss Vayo!

20
00:01:21,660 --> 00:01:23,150
I’m well aware of the situation.

21
00:01:23,150 --> 00:01:27,380
But I’m afraid those traitors will never let me return to Madelin alive.

22
00:01:27,400 --> 00:01:29,300
I didn’t expect you’d be here yourself, Mr. Henri.

23
00:01:31,800 --> 00:01:33,800
As I thought, it’s you, Chief.

24
00:01:34,400 --> 00:01:36,130
The car is coming to take you to the safehouse in Khao Yai.

25
00:01:36,259 --> 00:01:37,729
How do you feel about me?

26
00:01:38,060 --> 00:01:39,259
I love you.

27
00:01:39,560 --> 00:01:42,880
I truly appreciate it. But I’m afraid I can’t return the feelings.

28
00:01:43,700 --> 00:01:46,160
We’ll go back to Thailand to get rid of the princess.

29
00:01:46,759 --> 00:01:48,600
What grudges are you holding against the royal family?

30
00:01:49,000 --> 00:01:52,200
It’s none of your concern. Just do your best as a fake princess.

31
00:01:55,060 --> 00:01:57,360
You will visit Thailand again, Your Highness?

32
00:01:58,530 --> 00:01:59,330
Yes.

33
00:02:01,060 --> 00:02:02,980
But according to your schedule,

34
00:02:02,980 --> 00:02:07,550
you are to return to Madelin next week after finishing all engagements , Your Highness.

35
00:02:11,960 --> 00:02:16,329
I’d like to visit Thailand for a private leisure before going back to Madelin.

36
00:02:18,700 --> 00:02:21,530
Are you going to obstruct me in place of Father, Miss Isabelle?

37
00:02:24,000 --> 00:02:24,980
Not at all, Your Highness.

38
00:02:24,980 --> 00:02:27,280
I wouldn’t dare defy your will, Princess Blew.

39
00:02:27,960 --> 00:02:31,450
Then, please have it taken care of, Miss Isabelle.

40
00:02:32,460 --> 00:02:35,010
I will attend to it immediately, Your Highness.

41
00:02:51,060 --> 00:02:53,200
Having power in your hand is amazing, isn’t it?

42
00:02:55,100 --> 00:02:56,710
Wouldn’t it be too risky?

43
00:02:57,560 --> 00:02:59,550
But going back to Madelin this time,

44
00:02:59,980 --> 00:03:06,680
you’ll be taking over King Arthur’s throne as the appointed crown princess.

45
00:03:08,560 --> 00:03:11,400
And I can’t risk having this plan go wrong again.

46
00:03:13,060 --> 00:03:15,750
The princess won’t always be that lucky.

47
00:03:17,960 --> 00:03:23,410
If Henri fails again, I’ll take this matter into my own hands.

48
00:03:26,079 --> 00:03:29,510
[Normandy, France]

49
00:03:37,600 --> 00:03:41,510
I can’t believe something this serious is happening to my sister.

50
00:03:41,910 --> 00:03:47,010
No wonder why she seemed a bit off when I was on the phone with her last time.

51
00:03:47,500 --> 00:03:49,550
That was probably the imposter, Your Highness.

52
00:03:49,600 --> 00:03:51,000
Is my sister safe right now?

53
00:03:51,400 --> 00:03:56,310
Yes, Your Highness. Despite having to keep running away, she’s still safe.

54
00:03:56,310 --> 00:03:58,380
I’ll let Father know immediately.

55
00:03:58,810 --> 00:04:01,580
Please tell my sister to look after herself.

56
00:04:01,910 --> 00:04:03,910
I’ll find a way to help her as soon as I can.

57
00:04:04,530 --> 00:04:05,330
Yes, Your Highness.

58
00:04:20,730 --> 00:04:21,980
Have some tea first.

59
00:04:23,900 --> 00:04:24,700
Thank you.

60
00:04:36,700 --> 00:04:38,780
Are you mad at me, Miss Blew?

61
00:04:40,860 --> 00:04:41,800
Mad about what?

62
00:04:44,000 --> 00:04:47,610
Well, about…

63
00:05:06,160 --> 00:05:07,950
What are you doing here?

64
00:05:09,460 --> 00:05:11,610
I’m afraid you’d feel uncomfortable.

65
00:05:13,160 --> 00:05:14,500
Are you mad at me?

66
00:05:16,660 --> 00:05:21,050
It’s me who should’ve asked that–are you mad at me?

67
00:05:21,760 --> 00:05:24,860
Why would I? I’m the one who asked you first.

68
00:05:25,930 --> 00:05:27,510
I’m not mad at you.

69
00:05:28,210 --> 00:05:29,950
I’m actually afraid.

70
00:05:33,900 --> 00:05:35,110
Afraid of what?

71
00:05:37,300 --> 00:05:46,150
I’m afraid you might hate me–that I’d make you feel uncomfortable since you now know how I feel about you.

72
00:05:46,500 --> 00:05:48,560
But I’m still here with you.

73
00:05:49,300 --> 00:05:50,860
Do I look uncomfortable to you?

74
00:05:55,130 --> 00:06:01,180
Isn’t it funny? I’m the one who’s still the same but it’s you who has changed.

75
00:06:03,260 --> 00:06:07,930
How could I not? I just confessed to you.

76
00:06:10,860 --> 00:06:12,180
I know.

77
00:06:15,960 --> 00:06:18,560
But can you please stay the same to me?

78
00:06:19,700 --> 00:06:24,280
So that one day I might finally understand the meaning of love.

79
00:06:30,050 --> 00:06:31,010
Sure.

80
00:06:35,500 --> 00:06:43,460
If I do anything wrong or inappropriate to you, you can always say it, Miss Blew.

81
00:06:46,530 --> 00:06:52,180
If it makes me feel awkward, I’ll stop you and warn you myself.

82
00:07:04,500 --> 00:07:07,150
Miss Fah should have met Karel by now.

83
00:07:08,600 --> 00:07:15,550
Once Karel sees the letter, I’m sure he’ll tell Father and they’ll find a way to help us as soon as they can.

84
00:07:19,130 --> 00:07:22,200
And you’ll have to go back to Madelin after that.

85
00:07:26,200 --> 00:07:27,600
Madelin is my home.

86
00:07:31,400 --> 00:07:32,900
I’ll miss you a lot.

87
00:07:37,800 --> 00:07:39,950
Don’t you have airplanes in Thailand?

88
00:07:44,400 --> 00:07:45,200
I beg your pardon?

89
00:07:47,530 --> 00:07:51,250
Madelin might be far but you can always fly there to visit me.

90
00:07:51,700 --> 00:07:53,659
You’re more than welcome there.

91
00:07:54,500 --> 00:07:57,409
And I believe Father and Karel would also be pleased to welcome you,

92
00:07:57,409 --> 00:08:01,110
since you’re the one who has saved my life.

93
00:08:02,160 --> 00:08:08,410
What if I move to Madelin for good? Is there any job position for me there?

94
00:08:09,760 --> 00:08:14,380
We have plenty of royal guards there. I’d rather not bother you.

95
00:08:16,730 --> 00:08:19,580
What about other positions?

96
00:08:21,730 --> 00:08:23,410
Well, I’m not sure.

97
00:08:24,310 --> 00:08:30,110
Unlike Father, I still don’t have enough power to appoint any position to you at my own will.

98
00:08:31,730 --> 00:08:37,350
There’s no need to bother King Arthur for the position that I want.

99
00:08:44,550 --> 00:08:48,180
Let’s…go inside.

100
00:08:49,260 --> 00:08:52,310
Why did you help me when I fell off the boat that day?

101
00:08:59,360 --> 00:09:00,400
I don’t know.

102
00:09:01,500 --> 00:09:03,650
And I’m actually not good at swimming.

103
00:09:04,700 --> 00:09:06,450
That was very dangerous.

104
00:09:07,500 --> 00:09:08,780
I was shocked.

105
00:09:09,560 --> 00:09:14,350
Please don’t do that again, no matter how shocked you are.

106
00:09:16,660 --> 00:09:19,210
But your life is important too.

107
00:09:20,400 --> 00:09:22,660
My life means nothing compared to yours.

108
00:09:23,930 --> 00:09:31,680
If that time comes when I have to choose, even my life–I can sacrifice it for you.

109
00:09:32,300 --> 00:09:34,380
Don’t let me hear you say that again.

110
00:09:35,200 --> 00:09:38,250
Whether dead or alive, it’s my own life.

111
00:09:38,650 --> 00:09:42,480
I don’t want you to sacrifice your life for me anymore.

112
00:09:43,130 --> 00:09:47,750
I just want to protect you as someone who loves you.

113
00:09:50,800 --> 00:09:54,880
If you love me, then don’t die.

114
00:09:55,360 --> 00:09:57,500
Never say you’ll sacrifice your life for me again.

115
00:10:08,730 --> 00:10:09,530
I’m sorry.

116
00:10:15,560 --> 00:10:17,310
I’ll never say that again

117
00:10:24,060 --> 00:10:26,300
We will get through this together alive.

118
00:10:29,060 --> 00:10:35,000
I’ll wait for that day when you finally love me too.

119
00:10:55,160 --> 00:11:01,450
[Princess Blew]: If it makes me feel awkward, I’ll stop you and warn you myself.

120
00:11:11,460 --> 00:11:14,910
If you think I’d be mad, why did you do it?

121
00:11:18,600 --> 00:11:20,810
Because you didn’t stop me.

122
00:11:26,330 --> 00:11:27,300
I’m sorry.

123
00:11:29,600 --> 00:11:34,580
I’ll be more careful next time and won't do anything inappropriate again.

124
00:11:37,000 --> 00:11:39,760
So, you won’t do that again?

125
00:11:40,460 --> 00:11:45,360
No, I won’t. I will not kiss you like that again.

126
00:11:48,400 --> 00:11:52,910
What if I allow you to, will you do it?

127
00:11:55,200 --> 00:11:56,000
Huh?

128
00:12:07,660 --> 00:12:10,960
I still have no idea what love is.

129
00:12:15,660 --> 00:12:20,500
But I didn’t mind when you did that to me.

130
00:12:45,530 --> 00:12:46,330
What’s wrong?

131
00:12:48,560 --> 00:12:51,380
You just kissed me.

132
00:13:19,780 --> 00:13:23,780
[Thap Lan National Park]

133
00:13:28,330 --> 00:13:33,080
Right here. This is the main entrance they’d pick.

134
00:13:33,750 --> 00:13:35,810
Send in our sniper team.

135
00:13:36,210 --> 00:13:38,080
Well take them down there.

136
00:13:40,930 --> 00:13:43,200
Have you spread the news about the princess through Santi?

137
00:13:44,260 --> 00:13:45,260
All done, sir.

138
00:13:47,560 --> 00:13:56,560
Excuse me, sir. Why don’t you just send some of our men to help Chief Santi catch Henri?

139
00:13:58,500 --> 00:14:03,450
Because judging from the latest information I got from Santi about the fake princess returning to Thailand,

140
00:14:04,210 --> 00:14:12,080
I’m very positive all those attempts to assassinate Princess Blew are not Henri’s doing alone.

141
00:14:12,930 --> 00:14:14,600
I need to get all of them.

142
00:14:18,100 --> 00:14:19,410
Understood, sir.

143
00:14:26,760 --> 00:14:27,800
You have three days.

144
00:14:43,730 --> 00:14:44,860
I’ll be in touch.

145
00:14:58,500 --> 00:15:00,360
General Wathit wants to talk to you.

146
00:15:07,530 --> 00:15:08,330
Yes, sir.

147
00:15:10,530 --> 00:15:12,310
Everything is going according to the plan.

148
00:15:21,960 --> 00:15:24,610
Have you called for backups?

149
00:15:24,660 --> 00:15:26,000
They’ll be here by tomorrow morning.

150
00:15:26,660 --> 00:15:30,950
Now that we know where they are, why don’t we just go finish them tomorrow?

151
00:15:31,700 --> 00:15:32,500
Not yet.

152
00:15:33,100 --> 00:15:34,300
It might be a trap.

153
00:15:35,260 --> 00:15:37,750
They might have spread fake news to Santi.

154
00:15:38,730 --> 00:15:41,710
Go study all entrance and exit routes of that safehouse.

155
00:15:41,800 --> 00:15:44,980
When everything is ready, we’ll do it.

156
00:15:45,250 --> 00:15:46,050
Yes, sir.

157
00:16:09,500 --> 00:16:13,680
Dad said Henri already found out where we are.

158
00:16:15,360 --> 00:16:16,980
Do we have to run again?

159
00:16:17,660 --> 00:16:18,850
No.

160
00:16:20,400 --> 00:16:21,650
Then what?

161
00:16:26,160 --> 00:16:29,910
Dad will lure Henri here and arrest them all.

162
00:16:33,000 --> 00:16:36,550
I’m sorry for using you as bait, Miss Blew.

163
00:16:36,900 --> 00:16:39,250
But I don’t want both of us to run anymore.

164
00:16:45,500 --> 00:16:47,180
I’m willing to do it.

165
00:16:48,000 --> 00:16:50,710
But catching Henri won’t be easy.

166
00:16:51,260 --> 00:16:57,250
But if we can get him, Grace and the fake princess will lose all their bargaining power.

167
00:17:19,099 --> 00:17:22,109
Please don’t worry. I’ll make sure everyone is safe.

168
00:17:26,560 --> 00:17:30,210
Let’s get some sleep–get ourselves ready for tomorrow.

169
00:17:35,000 --> 00:17:38,050
Can I sleep while listening to your heartbeat?

170
00:17:40,300 --> 00:17:41,100
Yes?

171
00:17:43,730 --> 00:17:49,950
Once everything is over, I mightn’t be able to sleep next to you like this again.

172
00:17:52,260 --> 00:17:55,180
I want to memorise the sound of your heartbeat.

173
00:18:44,950 --> 00:18:47,650
[The Kingdom of Madelin]

174
00:18:50,130 --> 00:18:54,250
Can we contact the authorities in Thailand to handle this matter and arrest the traitors, Father?

175
00:18:55,760 --> 00:19:01,780
No. If they find out that I know about this, you might be in danger.

176
00:19:03,300 --> 00:19:08,080
Besides, we still don’t know if Sir Antoine is also involved.

177
00:19:08,750 --> 00:19:10,850
Let me make sure about it first.

178
00:19:15,100 --> 00:19:17,680
Will you consider my plan, Father

179
00:19:21,400 --> 00:19:22,480
I’m listening.

180
00:19:24,010 --> 00:19:27,250
[Taipei]

181
00:19:32,000 --> 00:19:34,360
You and Karel will come to Thailand, Father?

182
00:19:35,900 --> 00:19:42,880
Yes, so that we can have some family time before you’ll come back to take the throne as the Queen.

183
00:19:47,930 --> 00:19:50,150
But it’s boiling hot there, Father.

184
00:19:50,930 --> 00:19:55,750
That’s all right. I want to spend time with you and escort you home myself.

185
00:20:01,200 --> 00:20:03,410
Then, see you in Thailand, Father.

186
00:20:07,260 --> 00:20:08,500
Deal.

187
00:20:11,500 --> 00:20:12,810
What should we do now?

188
00:20:13,400 --> 00:20:14,850
What should we do?

189
00:20:17,730 --> 00:20:18,530
I’m out of here!

190
00:20:18,560 --> 00:20:19,200
Calm down.

191
00:20:19,200 --> 00:20:20,010
I’m out! I won’t do it!

192
00:20:20,010 --> 00:20:20,810
Stop!

193
00:20:21,660 --> 00:20:22,460
I won’t do it!

194
00:20:22,800 --> 00:20:24,100
We have to get rid of Blew.

195
00:20:26,860 --> 00:20:27,660
How?

196
00:20:45,700 --> 00:20:50,510
Henri, listen to me. King Arthur is going to Thailand.

197
00:20:50,600 --> 00:20:54,010
You need to get rid of Blew before he gets there.

198
00:20:54,500 --> 00:20:58,510
Don’t worry, I already know where Princess Blew is.

199
00:21:47,260 --> 00:21:49,550
This necklace represents my heart.

200
00:22:06,100 --> 00:22:11,950
Don’t you know the maximum sentence for offending the royal family is a death penalty?

201
00:22:16,260 --> 00:22:21,350
I’d rather be executed than letting you fall sick from getting cold.

202
00:22:23,500 --> 00:22:24,930
Are you cold?

203
00:22:25,760 --> 00:22:26,560
Nope.

204
00:22:31,300 --> 00:22:35,850
In Madelin, it snows every year.

205
00:22:38,300 --> 00:22:40,680
I want to see the snow in Madelin.

206
00:22:44,400 --> 00:22:48,410
The first snow will probably come in a while.

207
00:22:52,600 --> 00:22:58,150
When everything is over, let’s go see the snow in Madelin together.

208
00:23:08,760 --> 00:23:10,930
Want some cocoa? I made it for you.

209
00:23:12,930 --> 00:23:15,680
Cocoa? It’s my favourite drink.

210
00:23:15,960 --> 00:23:18,450
Then, you have to take me back to Madelin with you so you’ll have someone to–

211
00:23:18,450 --> 00:23:20,450
[Signal flare]
Then, you have to take me back to Madelin with you so you’ll have someone to–

212
00:23:22,130 --> 00:23:24,730
That’s from the resort. We need to get out of here.

213
00:23:25,300 --> 00:23:26,580
Let’s go.

214
00:23:28,330 --> 00:23:30,380
I told my team to wait on the other side of a creek.

215
00:23:30,960 --> 00:23:32,580
Please put this on.

216
00:23:33,760 --> 00:23:34,960
What about you?

217
00:23:35,360 --> 00:23:36,610
I have mine ready.

218
00:23:36,610 --> 00:23:37,550
[Signal flare]

219
00:23:39,000 --> 00:23:40,110
Please hurry up.

220
00:24:07,510 --> 00:24:09,550
[Gunfight]

221
00:24:22,700 --> 00:24:24,180
Drop your weapon!

222
00:24:25,450 --> 00:24:34,510
[Continuous shootout]

223
00:25:12,810 --> 00:25:14,350
[Police]: Let’s go! Quick!

224
00:25:14,950 --> 00:25:21,910
[Police]: Quick! Move it!

225
00:25:22,960 --> 00:25:26,410
We got all of them except Henri, sir.

226
00:25:32,180 --> 00:25:33,350
[Gunshot]

227
00:25:37,200 --> 00:25:38,330
Contact that team.

228
00:25:39,900 --> 00:25:44,110
B team, over! B team, over!

229
00:25:50,080 --> 00:25:51,550
[Gunshots]

230
00:26:00,400 --> 00:26:01,450
You two keep watch here.

231
00:26:01,450 --> 00:26:01,950
Yes, sir.

232
00:26:01,960 --> 00:26:02,910
The rest follow me.

233
00:26:11,750 --> 00:26:12,850
[Gunshot]

234
00:26:15,850 --> 00:26:21,280
[Gunfight]

235
00:26:39,300 --> 00:26:40,760
You’re not wearing a vest!

236
00:26:41,500 --> 00:26:42,460
You lied to me!

237
00:26:44,300 --> 00:26:45,260
I’m okay.

238
00:26:46,660 --> 00:26:48,260
But you’re bleeding a lot.

239
00:26:50,200 --> 00:26:52,280
Let’s hurry. Let’s go.

240
00:26:52,280 --> 00:26:53,280
Miss Vayo.

241
00:26:53,280 --> 00:26:54,150
Let’s go.

242
00:26:55,800 --> 00:26:59,110
[Hitman]: Drop the gun and hand her over.

243
00:26:59,600 --> 00:27:02,580
It’s you who should drop the gun.

244
00:27:07,530 --> 00:27:08,400
Drop the gun!

245
00:27:10,360 --> 00:27:11,160
Drop it!

246
00:27:18,500 --> 00:27:19,300
Drop it!

247
00:27:42,680 --> 00:27:43,610
[Gunshot]

248
00:27:44,010 --> 00:27:44,980
Miss Vayo!

249
00:27:51,310 --> 00:27:52,750
Miss Vayo!

250
00:28:05,680 --> 00:28:06,850
Miss Vayo!

251
00:28:22,050 --> 00:28:23,410
[Gunshot]

252
00:28:29,050 --> 00:28:31,080
Miss Vayo…

253
00:28:32,760 --> 00:28:33,950
[Henri]: Get up!

254
00:28:36,500 --> 00:28:37,580
Henri!

255
00:28:38,900 --> 00:28:40,280
Just  give up, Princess.

256
00:28:40,500 --> 00:28:41,930
I don’t want to hurt you.

257
00:28:43,000 --> 00:28:44,310
Put the gun down.

258
00:28:47,400 --> 00:28:49,680
Do it, Miss Blew! Let’s end this!

259
00:28:52,860 --> 00:28:54,850
I said put the gun down!

260
00:29:00,200 --> 00:29:02,610
Okay, okay! I’ll do it.

261
00:29:13,210 --> 00:29:14,180
Miss Vayo!

262
00:29:16,560 --> 00:29:17,360
Miss Vayo! Miss Vayo!

263
00:29:30,300 --> 00:29:31,980
Why don’t you just kill me?

264
00:29:35,660 --> 00:29:38,150
Grace will take care of you herself.

265
00:29:40,160 --> 00:29:40,960
Grace…

266
00:29:48,100 --> 00:29:48,650
Don’t!

267
00:29:48,650 --> 00:29:49,310
Come here!

268
00:29:49,310 --> 00:29:52,280
No! Don’t! No!

269
00:29:59,200 --> 00:30:01,210
Don’t! Don’t!

270
00:30:04,510 --> 00:30:05,210
[Gunshot]

271
00:30:05,210 --> 00:30:06,250
Stop!

272
00:30:07,680 --> 00:30:08,550
Move!

273
00:30:08,550 --> 00:30:10,950
Miss Vayo! Miss Vayo!

274
00:30:11,450 --> 00:30:15,510
[Continuous shootout]

275
00:30:31,000 --> 00:30:32,280
Lom!

276
00:31:03,100 --> 00:31:07,950
If you stop now, I promise I’ll convince Father to forgive you.

277
00:31:09,460 --> 00:31:12,450
I’ve come too far to turn back, Your Highness.

278
00:31:13,460 --> 00:31:15,750
You’ve changed so much.

279
00:31:16,110 --> 00:31:20,110
If Sir Antione knows, he’d be so disappointed in you.

280
00:31:20,130 --> 00:31:22,880
He has never been proud of me anyway.

281
00:31:23,660 --> 00:31:27,980
That’s not true. Mr. Antoine is very proud of you.

282
00:31:27,980 --> 00:31:37,150
He told Father that once I ascend the throne, he would resign and pass on his position to you.

283
00:31:38,260 --> 00:31:42,910
No, that’s not true. Don’t lie to me, Princess.

284
00:31:43,460 --> 00:31:44,880
I’m telling the truth.

285
00:31:54,130 --> 00:31:55,300
It doesn’t matter.

286
00:31:56,560 --> 00:31:59,250
You’ll never get to take the throne anyway.

287
00:32:00,860 --> 00:32:02,330
Tell our men to keep watch.

288
00:32:03,900 --> 00:32:06,310
Never let Princess Blew out of your sight.

289
00:32:07,450 --> 00:32:08,550
Yes, sir.

290
00:32:30,500 --> 00:32:31,480
Lom!

291
00:32:31,480 --> 00:32:34,450
Lom! Lom, are you okay?

292
00:32:36,460 --> 00:32:37,260
How are you feeling?

293
00:32:41,930 --> 00:32:43,310
Where’s Miss Blew?

294
00:32:50,560 --> 00:32:56,380
So? Is Miss Blew safe?

295
00:32:58,730 --> 00:33:03,980
Miss Blew.…They got her.

296
00:33:04,200 --> 00:33:05,010
What?

297
00:33:05,010 --> 00:33:05,910
But now, you’re–

298
00:33:05,930 --> 00:33:08,450
[Lom]: I have to help her!
[Fai]: Geez, calm down.

299
00:33:08,460 --> 00:33:10,250
Your wound might tear open.

300
00:33:15,100 --> 00:33:16,660
Have you looked at yourself?

301
00:33:17,000 --> 00:33:19,410
You’d only be a burden to them if you go now.

302
00:33:22,260 --> 00:33:24,860
I’m sure Miss Blew will be all right.

303
00:33:46,110 --> 00:33:50,710
[Phone ringing]

304
00:33:55,730 --> 00:33:57,330
You got the princess?

305
00:34:00,930 --> 00:34:06,600
Good, we’re in Thailand now–on our way to the meeting point. See you there.

306
00:34:09,699 --> 00:34:12,080
This is getting way too much for us to handle.

307
00:34:12,400 --> 00:34:13,460
I don’t want to do it anymore.

308
00:34:13,730 --> 00:34:19,510
If you quit now, the one who’ll die as a traitor is you.

309
00:34:42,850 --> 00:34:44,010
Grace!

310
00:34:54,560 --> 00:35:00,080
We have to hurry, before King Arthur and Prince Karel will be here tomorrow.

311
00:35:02,160 --> 00:35:02,960
Tomorrow?

312
00:35:03,360 --> 00:35:06,610
Yes, and Sir Antoine, your father too.

313
00:35:06,660 --> 00:35:09,010
This isn’t what we’ve planned, Grace.

314
00:35:09,130 --> 00:35:13,610
If my father and King Arthur find out, wouldn’t we all be executed?

315
00:35:20,500 --> 00:35:28,510
Henri, we’ve come this far. We can’t turn back now.

316
00:35:38,160 --> 00:35:42,650
Even if we kill the real princess and make Helena take her place,

317
00:35:43,360 --> 00:35:47,450
that cop, Vayo, will tell King Arthur everything anyway.

318
00:35:48,330 --> 00:35:51,080
I don’t think she’ll let her lover die for nothing.

319
00:35:54,500 --> 00:35:57,710
What? Who loves who?

320
00:36:00,330 --> 00:36:02,150
I said put the gun down!

321
00:36:03,610 --> 00:36:06,750
Okay, fine! I’ll do it!

322
00:36:08,750 --> 00:36:10,680
Miss Vayo! Miss Vayo!

323
00:36:20,360 --> 00:36:24,180
Are you sure it’s not just a cop doing her job to protect the princess?

324
00:36:25,160 --> 00:36:28,680
If it’s just that, she wouldn’t have given the princess a keepsake.

325
00:36:43,160 --> 00:36:43,960
[Henri]: Walk!

326
00:36:48,550 --> 00:36:48,950
[Princess Blew]: Let me go!

327
00:36:48,960 --> 00:36:50,150
Quiet!

328
00:36:57,660 --> 00:37:00,150
I’ve never seen you wear this necklace before, Princess.

329
00:37:02,530 --> 00:37:03,810
Don’t you dare!

330
00:37:24,800 --> 00:37:26,250
GPS.

331
00:37:28,330 --> 00:37:30,980
She must have put it on the princess to track her.

332
00:37:31,930 --> 00:37:33,330
But I already shut it off.

333
00:37:38,200 --> 00:37:39,660
If that’s true, then good.

334
00:37:42,860 --> 00:37:44,060
What are you planning to do?

335
00:38:08,130 --> 00:38:09,410
Grace.

336
00:38:14,200 --> 00:38:17,750
I’m so glad you still remember me.

337
00:38:19,860 --> 00:38:24,180
How could I forget the person who betrayed me?

338
00:38:24,860 --> 00:38:27,750
Father and everyone in the royal family have always been nice to you

339
00:38:29,100 --> 00:38:31,650
How can you do something so despicable to us?

340
00:38:37,330 --> 00:38:40,010
I want King Alderic to pay for what he did.

341
00:38:41,260 --> 00:38:46,080
The whole De Laina family must suffer the loss like I did.

342
00:38:46,900 --> 00:38:51,500
And you, as his beloved granddaughter, only have to pay for it.

343
00:38:54,160 --> 00:38:58,610
What did Grandfather do to make you feel so vengeful?

344
00:39:01,260 --> 00:39:09,180
Have you ever heard of a Bruzzo family who was wiped out entirely before King Aruther took his throne?

345
00:39:21,880 --> 00:39:28,550
[Lord, you are the God who saves me;]

346
00:39:29,010 --> 00:39:36,010
[day and night I cry out to you.]

347
00:39:36,910 --> 00:39:44,380
[May my prayer come before you;]

348
00:39:44,380 --> 00:39:51,980
[turn your ear to my cry.]

349
00:39:53,150 --> 00:39:59,480
[I am overwhelmed with troubles]

350
00:39:59,480 --> 00:40:09,910
[and my life draws near to death.]

351
00:40:10,480 --> 00:40:19,180
[Your wrath lies heavily on me;]

352
00:40:19,680 --> 00:40:27,180
[you have overwhelmed me with all your waves.]

353
00:40:27,180 --> 00:40:33,350
[I am confined and cannot escape;]

354
00:40:33,360 --> 00:40:42,250
[Grace]: I was the only one left. I did everything…to get myself a position at the palace.

355
00:40:33,360 --> 00:40:42,250
[my eyes are dim with grief.]

356
00:40:43,800 --> 00:40:48,710
[Grace]: And wait for the day to take my revenge on De Laina people, like what they did to us Bruzzo!

357
00:40:43,800 --> 00:40:51,350
[Your wrath has swept over me;]

358
00:40:51,810 --> 00:40:59,150
[your terrors have destroyed me.]

359
00:40:59,450 --> 00:41:07,010
[All day long they surround me like a flood;]

360
00:41:07,010 --> 00:41:08,910
[they have completely engulfed me.]

361
00:41:08,930 --> 00:41:13,510
[Grace]: All power shall fall into the hands of Bruzzo.

362
00:41:17,330 --> 00:41:22,210
[You have taken from me friend and neighbor—]

363
00:41:17,330 --> 00:41:22,210
And after that, I’ll kill each and everyone of you!

364
00:41:22,210 --> 00:41:29,310
[and now I’m only left…]

365
00:41:26,460 --> 00:41:29,350
- Please let it end with me.
- No!

366
00:41:31,730 --> 00:41:33,950
[with darkness (misery).]

367
00:41:31,730 --> 00:41:33,460
I won’t let you die so easily.

368
00:41:37,280 --> 00:41:38,950
What do you mean?

369
00:41:44,960 --> 00:41:53,650
I’ll make you feel the pain when you have to watch the ones you love die…

370
00:41:54,730 --> 00:41:57,080
without being able to do anything!

371
00:41:57,600 --> 00:41:59,250
I’ll make you suffer like I did!

372
00:42:23,500 --> 00:42:25,180
Lieutenant Vayo.

373
00:42:27,330 --> 00:42:29,710
She has nothing to do with this!

374
00:42:32,760 --> 00:42:34,780
You love her so much, don’t you?

375
00:42:35,100 --> 00:42:36,810
No, I don’t love her!

376
00:42:37,260 --> 00:42:43,580
So, if she has to die, I guess you wouldn’t feel anything then.

377
00:42:50,360 --> 00:42:52,250
Leave her alone!

378
00:43:13,200 --> 00:43:14,780
Please drop the formalities.

379
00:43:16,930 --> 00:43:23,110
King Arthur has spread words to trick the traitors that he’d arrive tomorrow, and asked me to escort him here in private.

380
00:43:25,930 --> 00:43:27,650
How is my sister?

381
00:43:31,360 --> 00:43:34,000
The police are tracking down her whereabouts.

382
00:43:35,100 --> 00:43:37,650
She has been captured, Your Majesty.

383
00:43:41,530 --> 00:43:43,500
Where is Miss Vayo now?

384
00:43:45,160 --> 00:43:48,880
My daughter was injured during the encounter.

385
00:43:49,180 --> 00:43:51,810
She is now in a hospital, Your Majesty.

386
00:43:58,160 --> 00:44:00,000
Excuse me, sir!

387
00:44:03,600 --> 00:44:04,550
What is it?

388
00:44:04,730 --> 00:44:06,710
Lieutenant Vayo has been missing.

389
00:44:11,130 --> 00:44:14,750
Check the surveillance cameras and have someone track her down right now!

390
00:44:15,400 --> 00:44:16,200
Yes, sir.

391
00:44:16,800 --> 00:44:18,510
What’s going on, General?

392
00:44:29,460 --> 00:44:32,660
Helping you sneak out like this, I’m a bit worried.

393
00:44:34,000 --> 00:44:36,460
But would you rather let her do it alone?

394
00:44:37,660 --> 00:44:39,080
It’d be more dangerous that way.

395
00:44:39,080 --> 00:44:41,380
Us coming with her is better.

396
00:44:41,660 --> 00:44:43,910
But what we’re going to do is extremely dangerous.

397
00:44:44,900 --> 00:44:47,810
Don’t you think we should tell your dad, Lom?

398
00:44:48,500 --> 00:44:51,600
If we tell him, there’s no way he’d let me go help Miss Blew.

399
00:44:53,600 --> 00:44:54,500
But what if–

400
00:44:54,700 --> 00:44:58,550
At least, let me find out where she is first. Then, I’ll tell Dad.

401
00:45:05,960 --> 00:45:07,580
I already turned it on.

402
00:45:09,300 --> 00:45:11,550
They should be here soon.

403
00:45:12,330 --> 00:45:15,710
Good. We can kill two birds with one stone.

404
00:45:20,560 --> 00:45:22,330
Have you got any sign of her?

405
00:45:23,260 --> 00:45:24,060
Not yet.

406
00:45:26,300 --> 00:45:27,610
What should we do now?

407
00:45:28,160 --> 00:45:30,300
Just go to where the signal was last seen.

408
00:45:32,300 --> 00:45:36,410
Hey! It’s the signal from her necklace!

409
00:45:45,060 --> 00:45:45,860
Don’t!

410
00:45:47,330 --> 00:45:49,330
Easy there, Miss Blew.

411
00:45:51,460 --> 00:45:54,450
That cop is willing to walk into a death trap herself.

412
00:45:55,060 --> 00:45:56,350
I said don’t!

413
00:45:57,600 --> 00:45:58,750
Helena!

414
00:46:00,900 --> 00:46:01,760
Keep an eye on her.

415
00:46:05,860 --> 00:46:08,310
Find something to blindfold and gag her too.

416
00:46:14,930 --> 00:46:16,380
Where are you going?

417
00:46:19,060 --> 00:46:23,730
I’ll go get ready to welcome Princess Blew’s important guest.

418
00:47:13,360 --> 00:47:15,110
You look exactly like me.

419
00:47:27,860 --> 00:47:29,310
Din, pull over here.

420
00:47:47,000 --> 00:47:49,000
I think the signal is coming from deep in the forest.

421
00:47:50,730 --> 00:47:56,260
Honestly, I think it’s strange. Why did the signal suddenly pop up? Is it a trap?

422
00:47:56,760 --> 00:48:02,580
I know. It might be a trap, but I still have to go. You and Fai just wait here.

423
00:48:02,580 --> 00:48:04,350
Just send this location to my dad.

424
00:48:04,710 --> 00:48:07,150
The backup team should be on their way.

425
00:48:07,730 --> 00:48:09,010
I’ll go with you.

426
00:48:09,010 --> 00:48:10,250
No, it’s too dangerous.

427
00:48:10,400 --> 00:48:13,300
Let her go with you. Two heads are better than one.

428
00:48:13,960 --> 00:48:16,960
Yeah. Don’t try to stop me, I’ll go anyway.

429
00:48:21,260 --> 00:48:22,250
Let’s go then.

430
00:48:44,130 --> 00:48:46,650
Lom just sent me the location of the suspects, Your Majesty.

431
00:48:47,730 --> 00:48:49,060
I’ll go help my sister too.

432
00:48:50,600 --> 00:48:53,500
Let’s leave that to General Wathit and Sir Antione.

433
00:48:56,560 --> 00:49:03,310
Please rest assured, Your Majesty. Should Henri try to do any harm to the princess and royal family,

434
00:49:03,710 --> 00:49:09,250
despite being my own son, I shall take him down with my own hands.

435
00:49:11,000 --> 00:49:15,380
I trust you. Please save my daughter.

436
00:49:26,330 --> 00:49:28,280
Helena, Grace wants you to–

437
00:49:40,000 --> 00:49:42,480
Grace! Helena’s gone!

438
00:49:46,060 --> 00:49:48,750
She probably got scared and ran away.

439
00:49:50,500 --> 00:49:51,680
I’ll go after her.

440
00:49:51,680 --> 00:49:53,250
No need.

441
00:49:53,910 --> 00:49:55,210
Just leave her.

442
00:49:55,610 --> 00:49:57,510
Let’s take care of Miss Blew first.

443
00:49:57,850 --> 00:49:59,950
We’ll get to that later.

444
00:50:02,700 --> 00:50:03,950
Excuse me, sir.

445
00:50:04,930 --> 00:50:09,080
Our informant said that Vayo is coming to this house.

446
00:50:12,000 --> 00:50:13,660
She’s really asking for it.

447
00:50:38,560 --> 00:50:39,650
Get up!

448
00:51:21,000 --> 00:51:21,900
Come here.

449
00:51:41,300 --> 00:51:42,500
Is it really this one?

450
00:51:42,930 --> 00:51:44,060
Why is it so quiet?

451
00:51:47,000 --> 00:51:48,110
It’s here.

452
00:51:56,610 --> 00:51:57,780
[GPS beeping]

453
00:52:00,360 --> 00:52:01,610
I’m going in.

454
00:52:02,880 --> 00:52:05,880
Don’t go in if the backup team isn’t here yet, got it?

455
00:52:05,960 --> 00:52:07,680
Do you want to get yourself killed?

456
00:52:07,680 --> 00:52:10,580
We already know where they are. Why don’t we just wait for backup first?

457
00:52:10,600 --> 00:52:12,800
They’re using Miss Blew to bargain with me.

458
00:52:14,000 --> 00:52:16,910
If we wait for backup, it’ll put Miss Blew in more danger.

459
00:52:16,960 --> 00:52:17,760
Wait here.

460
00:52:21,160 --> 00:52:22,360
Please be careful.

461
00:52:40,460 --> 00:52:47,450
Vayo, I know you’re around here.

462
00:52:52,200 --> 00:52:56,550
Come out. Don’t make your girl sacrifice herself for nothing.

463
00:53:09,660 --> 00:53:11,200
I’ll count to three.

464
00:53:16,400 --> 00:53:17,200
One!

465
00:53:24,260 --> 00:53:25,060
Two!

466
00:53:25,660 --> 00:53:26,880
I’m here.

467
00:53:38,130 --> 00:53:40,110
Walking right into your own death.

468
00:53:42,760 --> 00:53:45,050
It’s you who deserve to die, Traitor.

469
00:53:45,100 --> 00:53:46,310
How dare you!

470
00:53:47,730 --> 00:53:52,180
Grace, let’s finish this fast or else the cops might be here soon.

471
00:53:53,460 --> 00:53:56,080
If you’re hesitating, I’ll do it instead.

472
00:53:59,280 --> 00:53:59,980
[Gunshot]

473
00:54:10,150 --> 00:54:13,450
Grace! Why did you shoot me?

474
00:54:15,000 --> 00:54:21,610
Haven’t I told you to mind your own business? I’ll kill her myself!

475
00:54:30,860 --> 00:54:32,700
It’s your turn now, Vayo.

476
00:54:34,860 --> 00:54:39,650
Come out! I said come out!

477
00:54:52,130 --> 00:54:53,810
Don’t hurt her.

478
00:55:03,000 --> 00:55:06,580
Time to watch your loved one die right before your eyes.

479
00:55:09,510 --> 00:55:11,850
[Gunfight]

480
00:55:14,660 --> 00:55:16,850
Go in! Go!

481
00:55:16,860 --> 00:55:17,450
[Princess Blew]: No!

482
00:55:19,310 --> 00:55:21,710
[Grace]: Go in!
- [Princess Blew]: No!

483
00:55:21,730 --> 00:55:23,450
[Grace]: I said go in!
[Princess Blew]: No!

484
00:55:23,460 --> 00:55:23,980
[Grace]: Go!

485
00:55:23,980 --> 00:55:27,480
[Princess Blew]: No! Let me go!

486
00:55:47,960 --> 00:55:50,180
Go in! Go!

487
00:56:03,400 --> 00:56:06,380
[Police]: Freeze! Drop the gun and turn yourself in!

488
00:56:13,300 --> 00:56:14,950
[Lom]: It’s over, Grace.

489
00:56:20,560 --> 00:56:24,050
Shut up! This isn’t over yet!

490
00:56:24,130 --> 00:56:25,850
But you have no one left.

491
00:56:26,200 --> 00:56:28,910
Henri just took the bullets for you because he loved you.

492
00:56:29,160 --> 00:56:32,780
That’s because he’s a fool! He thought I loved him.

493
00:56:36,000 --> 00:56:40,850
Just like you, who’s willing to die for something stupid like love.

494
00:56:42,060 --> 00:56:45,810
It’s those who see love as something stupid that are actually stupid.

495
00:56:46,130 --> 00:56:48,080
You don’t get to patronize me!

496
00:56:48,080 --> 00:56:49,610
[Gunfight]

497
00:56:51,050 --> 00:56:52,380
[Continuous shootout]

498
00:57:18,500 --> 00:57:19,910
Miss Blew!

499
00:57:55,730 --> 00:57:56,560
Miss Blew!

500
00:58:00,900 --> 00:58:02,080
Miss Blew!

501
00:58:02,360 --> 00:58:03,580
Miss Blew!

502
00:58:06,500 --> 00:58:11,350
[Princess Blew]: Please don’t get hurt because of me again.

503
00:58:11,560 --> 00:58:13,750
[Lom]: I can’t promise that.

504
00:58:14,500 --> 00:58:16,860
But there’s one thing I can.

505
00:58:18,700 --> 00:58:24,910
[Lom]: As long as I’m here, I’ll never let anyone hurt you.

506
00:58:26,260 --> 00:58:30,280
I’ll protect you with my own life.

507
00:58:33,700 --> 00:58:35,780
How do you feel about me?

508
00:58:37,800 --> 00:58:39,350
I love you.

509
00:58:39,780 --> 00:58:53,380
♫They mean so much to me. Stay with me, please don’t go♫

510
00:58:54,050 --> 00:59:00,480
♫All my heart, there’s only you♫

511
00:59:00,480 --> 00:59:08,850
♫Stay with me, now and forever♫

512
